				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Conventionally, the hardwired controllers on an original Famicom (or the ones plugged into the front ports on the AV model) are numbered 1 and 2, and the plug-in controllers 3 and 4. Player 1 may use controller 1 (first hardwired controller) or 3 (first plug-in controller), and player 2 may use controller 2 or 4. As I understand it, only a four-player game treats all four as distinct input sources.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

